Westfield also recorded four special teams tackles in 2010., 26992=Personal - a health promotions major here at Southern...born September 1, 1990 in Neosho, Mo...son of Anthony and Sherri Westfield...has one sister, Karynda., 26251=In High School - a 2009 graduate from Neosho HS, Westfield helped the Wildcats to both 2008 district and a regional championships...he was a 3 year starter for Coach Shawn Flanningan at linebacker/wide receiver as well as a three year starter at rightfield/pitcher in baseball for Coach Eddie Crupper...Westfield earned first team All-Conference accolades as a linebacker during both junior and senior campaigns...he also earned first team All-District as a linebacker and punter and second team All-Conference as a punter...Westfield was selected as 1230AM The Fan first team linebacker...he was aslo both a first team All-Conference and second team All-District rightfielder., 25850=2011- A bulldozer near the goaline, the sophomore fullback ran for nine yards on seven carries and five touchdowns, including two apiece vs Emporia State and Fort Hays State., 25509=2012 - Playing in five games at linebacker for the Lions as a junior, Westfield made the transition to defense after playing his first two years on offense finishing the year with three tackles, all solo, including making a pair of tackles in the Lions' homecoming win over South Dakota School of Mines.}
